mistral.reason: Edouard Balladur was not the president of Georges Pompidou. Instead, Balladur served as an advisor and cabinet member under Georges Pompidou, holding positions such as under-secretary general of the presidency and secretary general from 1973 to Pompidou's death in 1974. Additionally, Georges Pompidou was a President of France himself, not the other way around.

gemma2.reason: Several passages state Balladur worked *for* Pompidou, holding positions like advisor and secretary general during Pompidou's time as President.   A president cannot also be the president of another person.

llama3.1.reason: The claim is wrong because Édouard Balladur was an advisor to Georges Pompidou, but he never held the office of President.

qwen2.5.reason: Édouard Balladur was a political advisor to Georges Pompidou and served as his under-secretary general of the presidency, but he never became president. Georges Pompidou was the President of France from 1969 to 1974.
